            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18010520-73-person577">
                  JOHN 
                  EDWARDS
               <interp inst="t18010520-73-person577" type="surname" value="EDWARDS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18010520-73-person577" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18010520-73-person577" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am <rs id="t18010520-73-viclabel400" type="occupation">butler</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18010520-73-victim576 t18010520-73-viclabel400"></join> to Mr. Rowe, <placeName id="t18010520-73-crimeloc401">Lower Berkeley-street, Portman-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18010520-73-crimeloc401" type="placeName" value="Lower Berkeley-street, Portman-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18010520-73-crimeloc401" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18010520-73-off398 t18010520-73-crimeloc401"></join>; I lost a coat on the 28th of April, but I was not at home at the time it was taken; I saw it about ten o'clock in the morning in the pantry; when I came home I found the prisoner in custody; I know the coat to be mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18010520-73-person578">
                  SAMUEL 
                  SLATER
               <interp inst="t18010520-73-person578" type="surname" value="SLATER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18010520-73-person578" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18010520-73-person578" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am footman to Mr. Rowe; I saw the prisoner come out of the pantry with the coat on his arm; the pantry is at the bottom of the area steps; I followed him up the area steps, and took him opposite the street-door; I brought him back into the pantry, and afterwards into the hall; then I sent for a constable, and he was taken to Marlborough-street. (Produces the coat).</p>
               <p>Edwards. This is my coat.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I purchased the coat of a Jew, in Baker-street, Portman-square, and was going home with it; I went down this area to enquire for a young man I wanted to see.</p>
               <p>Q.(To Slater). Did you hear him make any enquiries there? - A. No; I had not left the pantry door one minute when I took the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18010520-73-verdict402" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18010520-73-verdict402" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 33.</p>
